cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.IR 

This paper involves natural language processing (NLP) and deep learning-based methods for extracting spatial information from radiology reports. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves the use of bidirectional long short-term memory (Bi-LSTM) conditional random field (CRF) model, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper deals with chest X-ray reports, which involves image analysis (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR) to some extent.
